				\begin{document}$$V_{\text {DC}}$$\end{document} at a predefined target value and the energy sharing between the parallel connected components (Figs. 1, 4). The use of several components and thus multiple DC/DC converters increases the difficulty of observability and controllability.Fig. 1.
Decentralized Battery Management (DBMS) system architecture consisting of battery, generator and load nodes. The control is distributed in a local and global level.

The main control objective of the DBMS is to maintain the DC power line voltage VDC\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
